1
00:00:39,831 --> 00:00:41,332
If not me, then who?

2
00:00:41,416 --> 00:00:43,626
Surprise!

3
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:47,547
Dear, please understand your father.

4
00:00:47,630 --> 00:00:49,466
He's just worried about you.

5
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:53,511
But not in every situation
should you rely on a gun.

6
00:00:55,180 --> 00:00:56,222
<i>But you know, you're right.</i>

7
00:01:01,436 --> 00:01:03,897
<i>He has a new lead on our case.</i>

8
00:01:14,616 --> 00:01:16,868
Choose Senator Quintin!

9
00:01:16,951 --> 00:01:19,370
You can guarantee that we can rely on him!

10
00:01:19,454 --> 00:01:22,290
In service, you won't be left hanging!

11
00:01:22,373 --> 00:01:25,835
A sure win for our nation!

12
00:01:33,384 --> 00:01:35,470
Please sit down. Please sit down.

13
00:01:38,848 --> 00:01:42,519
Senator Quintin
is our asset in the Senate.

14
00:01:43,645 --> 00:01:47,148
Because of him, we're able
to secure a huge budget

15
00:01:47,232 --> 00:01:49,359
to support our operations.

16
00:01:50,151 --> 00:01:52,695
The great success of our agency

17
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,197
is because of him.

18
00:01:54,697 --> 00:01:57,700
Yes! Norberto is right.

19
00:01:58,743 --> 00:02:01,037
Just think of me as your bank.

20
00:02:01,955 --> 00:02:05,333
Because I have an interest in all of you.

21
00:02:13,424 --> 00:02:16,719
Bank, then, interest!

22
00:02:22,016 --> 00:02:25,145
You know? I have a lot of bank jokes.

23
00:02:36,447 --> 00:02:37,740
It made me cry!

24
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:54,382
So serious that I could marry this matter.

25
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:05,393
Sorry, sir, I just thought
it was still joke time.

26
00:03:08,521 --> 00:03:10,523
This is a serious matter.

27
00:03:11,524 --> 00:03:15,278
Because this is about Congressman Salazar!

28
00:03:18,406 --> 00:03:21,618
Congressman Salazar is an ally.

29
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:23,536
- You know that.
- Yes.

30
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,538
My political ally.

31
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,791
<i>Our bond has become so deep already.</i>

32
00:03:30,460 --> 00:03:33,129
We've already attended so many funerals,

33
00:03:33,212 --> 00:03:36,925
weddings, and christenings together.

34
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,218
But…

35
00:03:38,301 --> 00:03:43,139
there are rumors
about party-list representative Salazar.

36
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:54,108
<i>The truth is, the one</i>
<i>they call "The Good Congressman"</i>

37
00:03:54,192 --> 00:03:58,655
<i>is only pretending</i>
<i>that he is an anti-crime advocate.</i>

38
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,031
<i>But the truth is,</i>

39
00:04:00,114 --> 00:04:03,576
<i>he is the leader of a local syndicate</i>

40
00:04:03,660 --> 00:04:05,703
<i>called the "Sinigang Cartel".</i>

41
00:04:06,454 --> 00:04:08,164
<i>It was called the Sinigang Cartel</i>

42
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:11,876
<i>because their group</i>
<i>has many ingredients in the mix.</i>

43
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:17,006
Politicians, businessmen,
and street operators.

44
00:04:17,590 --> 00:04:19,759
So when the Moravianos
arrived in the country,

45
00:04:19,842 --> 00:04:22,262
this group was threatened,

46
00:04:22,345 --> 00:04:24,305
and Congressman Salazar

47
00:04:24,389 --> 00:04:28,434
tried to undermine the Moravianos
by using his power

48
00:04:29,018 --> 00:04:31,187
and influence in Congress.

49
00:04:32,146 --> 00:04:33,439
The result?

50
00:04:34,315 --> 00:04:36,776
The Moravianos silenced Salazar.

51
00:04:39,404 --> 00:04:40,446
Now,

52
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:44,826
I'm afraid that a war is coming

53
00:04:44,909 --> 00:04:49,163
between two large and violent syndicates.

54
00:04:50,665 --> 00:04:52,667
The Moravianos on the one hand.

55
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:55,878
The Sinigang Cartel on the other one.

56
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:08,975
Okay.

57
00:05:48,347 --> 00:05:50,725
Why are there so many weirdos
in this university?

58
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:54,645
Anyway, Angelito.

59
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:56,814
Just focus.

60
00:05:57,440 --> 00:05:58,274
Okay.

61
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:01,152
Okay.

62
00:06:02,528 --> 00:06:05,281
Why couldn't he just be honest?

63
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:07,658
Instead of already being
in her gown and all,

64
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:10,912
then running away from the church,

65
00:06:11,454 --> 00:06:13,915
he could’ve just texted her instead.

66
00:06:13,998 --> 00:06:15,166
"Hey, love.

67
00:06:15,249 --> 00:06:18,252
I think we shouldn't go through
with our wedding

68
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:21,506
because there's a sniper rifle
aimed at you.

69
00:06:21,589 --> 00:06:27,053
Because of my Italian best friend
who turns out to be obsessed with me."

70
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:28,471
Right?

71
00:06:28,554 --> 00:06:30,139
But he didn't do that.

72
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:33,559
That's why Tintin is so mad at him,

73
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:36,562
because she thought she was left
at the altar for no reason.

74
00:06:36,646 --> 00:06:38,523
She doesn't know that he did that

75
00:06:39,107 --> 00:06:42,193
because he's sacrificing his own happiness

76
00:06:42,944 --> 00:06:44,695
just so she can live.

77
00:06:46,155 --> 00:06:49,075
Sweetheart, I told you, didn't I?

78
00:06:49,158 --> 00:06:51,494
We're watching a great love story.

79
00:06:51,577 --> 00:06:52,954
You can see it yourself.

80
00:06:53,037 --> 00:06:54,997
It really is a super great love story.

81
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:58,042
It's just not logical,
but it's still great.

82
00:06:58,918 --> 00:06:59,961
True.

83
00:07:04,048 --> 00:07:09,053
That's why you fall in love.
Because you love.

84
00:07:49,177 --> 00:07:51,596
Hello? Who's this?

85
00:07:53,598 --> 00:07:54,640
Hello, ma'am!

86
00:08:01,439 --> 00:08:03,191
Why? What do you need from him?

87
00:08:08,112 --> 00:08:13,117
And I just want to say that Mr. Pinagpala
has qualified for a personal loan

88
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:17,413
that he can use for travel,
home improvement, medical expenses,

89
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:19,582
<i>and other personal plans!</i>

90
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:28,174
Let's just see each other tomorrow.

91
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:29,133
Huh?

92
00:08:30,384 --> 00:08:31,302
Oh, no!

93
00:08:32,011 --> 00:08:34,722
Why? Okay, I'll take you home.

94
00:08:34,805 --> 00:08:35,932
No need.

95
00:08:36,015 --> 00:08:37,892
I know you're tired, too.

96
00:08:37,975 --> 00:08:39,352
You need to rest.

97
00:08:39,435 --> 00:08:40,269
Chiara…

98
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,441
I'm sorry.

99
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:51,906
Why are you apologizing?

100
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,576
I'm not made of stone.

101
00:08:56,577 --> 00:08:57,995
I know that

102
00:08:58,579 --> 00:09:00,998
you're already frustrated
with our relationship.

103
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,125
You're right, anyway.

104
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:07,338
I have so much on my mind.
I’ve been doing a lot of things.

105
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:10,508
And the one I'm sacrificing

106
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:13,094
is you.

107
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:20,726
Well, I can't really blame you either.

108
00:09:23,062 --> 00:09:25,856
Because I was the one
who put you in that situation. So…

109
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:31,946
I guess that's really
how it's supposed to be, right?

110
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:35,783
We can't dictate fate,

111
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:38,703
who we get to meet in life.

112
00:09:51,841 --> 00:09:53,634
Like when we first met.

113
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:57,263
Okay.

114
00:09:57,346 --> 00:09:58,431
What's the deal?

115
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:03,811
First, do everything you need to do.

116
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:11,277
So that you won't need
to think about me for now.

117
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:14,572
But when you’re done,

118
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:16,115
when you're okay again,

119
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:19,535
you'll take me all over the world.

120
00:10:20,286 --> 00:10:23,122
We'll travel the whole world,
just the two of us.

121
00:10:46,646 --> 00:10:47,480
Bok!

122
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:50,441
What are you doing?

123
00:10:51,025 --> 00:10:54,153
Why did you sound like you're doing
a loan shark business?

124
00:10:54,236 --> 00:10:56,572
I told you, call Mikoy

125
00:10:56,656 --> 00:11:00,284
because he needs
to get this new information.

126
00:11:00,368 --> 00:11:02,203
Chiara was the one who answered.

127
00:11:05,956 --> 00:11:08,000
They're together right now.

128
00:11:08,959 --> 00:11:11,253
Maybe they're all lovey-dovey.

129
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:16,384
I think we need to restore
the surveillance inside Mikoy's condo.

130
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:19,553
Mikoy doesn't like being watched.

131
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:23,265
So we need to be careful
when we call or contact him.

132
00:11:23,849 --> 00:11:25,851
So our asset won't be compromised.

133
00:11:41,492 --> 00:11:42,368
Let's go.

134
00:11:46,914 --> 00:11:47,748
Hey.

135
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:49,583
What happened to the person

136
00:11:49,667 --> 00:11:52,920
who gets mad whenever
his privacy gets violated?

137
00:11:53,003 --> 00:11:55,798
But when it comes to the bullies,
he can’t do anything.

138
00:11:57,425 --> 00:11:59,176
Why do you care about my life?

139
00:12:00,428 --> 00:12:01,429
Ouch!

140
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:05,015
You know? You're hurting my feelings.

141
00:12:05,724 --> 00:12:07,685
We've been sleeping together
for several nights now.

142
00:12:07,768 --> 00:12:10,521
So, of course, I'm concerned about you.

143
00:12:12,690 --> 00:12:14,150
You can see it now, right?

144
00:12:14,233 --> 00:12:16,444
You can see what I have to deal with.

145
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:19,864
So, please. Don't add to it anymore.

146
00:12:19,947 --> 00:12:21,240
I already have so much on my mind.

147
00:12:21,323 --> 00:12:24,118
I don't know what to do
if you pile on too.

148
00:12:24,201 --> 00:12:25,786
I'm just being a friend

149
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:28,330
who's willing to help you
with those bullies.

150
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:30,541
You know?

151
00:12:31,167 --> 00:12:33,586
Asking others for help is not a weakness.

152
00:12:34,628 --> 00:12:37,798
And no joke. Just say it,
and I'll punch that Owen guy.

153
00:12:38,674 --> 00:12:39,633
What?

154
00:12:40,968 --> 00:12:42,261
There's no need.

155
00:12:43,471 --> 00:12:46,974
Don't get involved anymore.
And don't add yourself to the mess either.

156
00:12:47,975 --> 00:12:49,143
I can handle this.

157
00:14:00,589 --> 00:14:04,051
We thought the Philippines
was just one of their many branches.

158
00:14:05,094 --> 00:14:07,805
Turns out these Moravianos
are even more ambitious.

159
00:14:10,015 --> 00:14:12,518
Do you remember
Congressman Celestino Salazar?

160
00:14:12,601 --> 00:14:16,564
We have a very reliable source
saying that he was killed

161
00:14:16,647 --> 00:14:18,857
because he wasn't
investigating the Moravianos.

162
00:14:18,941 --> 00:14:21,944
Literally, he was their rival syndicate.

163
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:25,781
And apparently, our good congressman here
is the leader of the rival gang.

164
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:28,075
Its name is the Sinigang Cartel.

165
00:14:28,158 --> 00:14:28,993
So sour!

166
00:14:29,076 --> 00:14:30,286
It’s really sour!

167
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:31,829
Especially their operations.

168
00:14:31,912 --> 00:14:35,249
Illegal gambling, trafficking,
prostitution,

169
00:14:35,332 --> 00:14:36,625
gun running, name it.

170
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:39,545
But what's really even more sour
are our friends here.

171
00:14:42,089 --> 00:14:44,717
Because they want to rule
here in the Philippines.

172
00:15:02,151 --> 00:15:03,444
Who did this?

173
00:15:03,527 --> 00:15:05,321
Newcomers.

174
00:15:05,404 --> 00:15:06,947
Outsiders.

175
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:09,658
They go by the name of Moraviano.

176
00:15:16,081 --> 00:15:17,833
With interest, too!

177
00:15:19,877 --> 00:15:22,546
But why do they want
to rule here in the Philippines?

178
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:23,964
Well, in recent years,

179
00:15:24,048 --> 00:15:26,717
there's been a heavy crackdown
on organized crime in Europe.

180
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,928
So life became harder for them in Prague,

181
00:15:29,011 --> 00:15:31,221
or the whole Czech Republic.

182
00:15:32,389 --> 00:15:34,808
They want to move their operations here.

183
00:15:34,892 --> 00:15:38,062
Because here in the Philippines,
life is easier for them.

184
00:15:39,396 --> 00:15:41,649
And aren't we known all over the world?

185
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:44,443
We are the most hospitable country
in the world.

186
00:15:44,526 --> 00:15:46,820
Unfortunately, we welcome criminals.

187
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:49,073
And sometimes, we even vote for them.

188
00:15:49,907 --> 00:15:52,868
That's why they say,
"It's more fun in the Philippines."

189
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:14,640
Especially now that there’s a new base
of operations for the Moravianos.

190
00:16:25,275 --> 00:16:26,902
Not just for you,

191
00:16:26,986 --> 00:16:28,654
but also for Mikoy.

192
00:16:28,737 --> 00:16:32,116
He's been working so hard at Vertex.

193
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:36,704
So, he deserves to be celebrated too.

194
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:40,207
Well, I think he'll like that, Papa.

195
00:17:11,113 --> 00:17:12,364
Agent Alex,

196
00:17:12,448 --> 00:17:14,908
I… I have a problem.

197
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:16,827
I need your help.

198
00:17:17,661 --> 00:17:21,373
Mikoy, all you need to do
is continue working at Vertex.

199
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:26,295
And I'm sure there are
other people inside the Moravianos

200
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:28,714
who know about their illegal operations.

201
00:17:28,797 --> 00:17:31,050
Wait, this isn't about Vertex.

202
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,803
If this is about the Sinigang Cartel,

203
00:17:34,887 --> 00:17:36,847
you shouldn't worry about it.

204
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:38,724
We are monitoring them as well.

205
00:17:38,807 --> 00:17:40,976
And we think they won't retaliate anymore

206
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,895
because they've been crippled
by the Moravianos.

207
00:17:42,978 --> 00:17:44,855
There you go again,
always thinking about work.

208
00:17:44,938 --> 00:17:46,732
This isn't about work.

209
00:17:47,274 --> 00:17:49,234
I just wanted to ask something.

210
00:17:50,152 --> 00:17:51,653
About…

211
00:17:53,363 --> 00:17:54,823
About Chiara.

212
00:17:56,366 --> 00:17:57,743
What is Chiara’s problem?

213
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:04,541
All my plates are wrong!

214
00:18:05,042 --> 00:18:07,586
I thought you were smart!
I thought you were good!

215
00:18:07,669 --> 00:18:09,713
Why did I only get barely passing grades?

216
00:18:09,797 --> 00:18:11,924
You sabotaged my grades!

217
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:14,384
I didn’t have enough time.

218
00:18:15,928 --> 00:18:18,430
I also have my own assignments to finish.

219
00:18:18,514 --> 00:18:19,556
Hey.

220
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:22,476
I don't care about your assignments.

221
00:18:22,559 --> 00:18:26,980
Next time, you focus
on everything I make you do.

222
00:18:27,564 --> 00:18:29,233
Because this is your last chance.

223
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,111
If you mess up again,

224
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:34,404
you'll go through something
even worse than this.

225
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:35,364
Okay?!

226
00:18:41,161 --> 00:18:42,079
Leave!

227
00:18:43,664 --> 00:18:44,832
Hurry up!

228
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,209
So slow.

229
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:48,377
Move faster!

230
00:18:49,294 --> 00:18:50,712
Leave, I said!

231
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:54,299
‪Wow.

232
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:55,342
You're really something else.

233
00:18:57,344 --> 00:18:59,012
He’s so frustrating.

234
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:01,473
Excuse me!

235
00:19:01,557 --> 00:19:04,726
I just want to tell you all
to stop bothering Angelito.

236
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:07,146
And from now on,

237
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:09,940
you will do your own coursework.

238
00:19:10,023 --> 00:19:13,235
And none of you are allowed to bully him.

239
00:19:13,318 --> 00:19:16,321
- Understood?!
- She’s nothing.

240
00:19:16,405 --> 00:19:19,032
Who are you? Are you his bodyguard?

241
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:23,954
Something like that.

242
00:19:24,538 --> 00:19:27,332
- Well then, boys?
- She's brave.

243
00:19:27,416 --> 00:19:29,418
Let’s see if she's got what it takes.

244
00:19:39,344 --> 00:19:41,305
What about you?! You want to fight, huh?!

245
00:19:48,645 --> 00:19:50,731
You know, I feel guilty about her.

246
00:19:51,773 --> 00:19:53,817
Even in this situation,

247
00:19:55,402 --> 00:19:56,945
she’s still special to me.

248
00:19:58,071 --> 00:20:00,699
Just because I’m spying
on her mom and dad,

249
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:03,076
it doesn’t mean I stopped
caring about her.

250
00:20:04,494 --> 00:20:09,249
Of course, I still want
to protect our relationship.

251
00:20:10,459 --> 00:20:12,169
So, what’s the problem?

252
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:16,173
I just want to make it up to her.

253
00:20:16,882 --> 00:20:17,966
You know?

254
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:21,178
Do something… special for her.

255
00:20:22,846 --> 00:20:24,139
Why are you asking me?

256
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:26,266
Because you’re a girl.

257
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:27,851
So, what could it be?

258
00:20:29,269 --> 00:20:31,939
What could it be?
What would make her happy?

259
00:20:32,564 --> 00:20:34,608
Any suggestions? Come on.

260
00:20:34,691 --> 00:20:37,152
Give her flowers, chocolates.

261
00:20:38,528 --> 00:20:41,573
Wrong answer!
Flowers and chocolates again?

262
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:43,200
Is there really nothing else?

263
00:20:43,283 --> 00:20:44,576
There’s no originality.

264
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:47,537
It’s like it lacks imagination.

265
00:20:49,289 --> 00:20:50,582
Designer bags?

266
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:52,000
Designer shoes?

267
00:20:53,710 --> 00:20:54,795
Wrong answer again!

268
00:20:54,878 --> 00:20:56,797
Isn’t she rich?

269
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:59,132
And her parents are part of a syndicate.

270
00:20:59,216 --> 00:21:02,177
Do you think they’ll be impressed
by designer stuff?

271
00:21:02,261 --> 00:21:03,470
No.

272
00:21:04,972 --> 00:21:06,807
Go on a vacation together.

273
00:21:09,393 --> 00:21:10,727
No.

274
00:21:10,811 --> 00:21:13,105
Hold on. Have you ever been in love?

275
00:21:16,566 --> 00:21:19,987
It seems you don't have
any romance in your bones.

276
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:24,533
After years of being undercover,

277
00:21:24,616 --> 00:21:27,494
do you think I still
have time for hookups?

278
00:21:27,577 --> 00:21:28,620
Woah.

279
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:31,915
You know, I don’t want to judge,

280
00:21:31,999 --> 00:21:33,583
but I’ll judge you.

281
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:35,836
Your life sounds kind of sad.

282
00:21:37,254 --> 00:21:41,550
My happiness isn’t about
whether I have a man or not.

283
00:21:41,633 --> 00:21:44,261
My happiness is putting criminals in jail.

284
00:21:45,512 --> 00:21:48,432
You know, they should build you a statue.

285
00:21:48,515 --> 00:21:49,766
You’re something else.

286
00:21:54,021 --> 00:21:55,689
Have you ever thought about it?

287
00:21:55,772 --> 00:21:58,233
That if Chiara discovers the truth,

288
00:21:58,317 --> 00:22:01,028
that you’re spying on her parents,

289
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:02,404
she’ll get heartbroken?

290
00:22:06,575 --> 00:22:09,619
I don’t want to be the bearer
of bad news, Mikoy,

291
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:13,248
but once the truth comes out,

292
00:22:14,541 --> 00:22:17,669
it’s possible that your relationship
won’t survive.

293
00:22:19,921 --> 00:22:21,590
Of course, I’ve thought about it.

294
00:22:22,507 --> 00:22:25,385
That’s why I’m thinking
of romantic moments, right?

295
00:22:25,469 --> 00:22:27,304
Something big and different.

296
00:22:27,387 --> 00:22:30,807
So that somehow, when she finds out
I’ve been lying to her…

297
00:22:32,434 --> 00:22:35,729
I hope she remembers
the happy moments we’ve had together.

298
00:22:37,564 --> 00:22:39,775
Even though I’m pretending to be an agent,

299
00:22:39,858 --> 00:22:42,569
well, she knows that,

300
00:22:43,779 --> 00:22:46,948
you know… that I’m true to her.

301
00:22:49,576 --> 00:22:50,869
My heart is real.

302
00:22:58,001 --> 00:22:59,169
Right?

303
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:04,674
Do you watch K-dramas?

304
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:48,093
Sweetheart?

305
00:23:50,137 --> 00:23:52,389
- Is there a problem?
- Huh?

306
00:23:53,014 --> 00:23:54,432
No, there’s no problem.

307
00:23:55,433 --> 00:23:56,268
I just finished early today.

308
00:23:56,351 --> 00:23:59,646
That’s why I wanted to see you.

309
00:24:01,106 --> 00:24:02,983
- Wow!
- What?

310
00:24:03,066 --> 00:24:06,695
Mr. Busy Man has time now!

311
00:24:07,279 --> 00:24:09,656
I was about to get mad at you.

312
00:24:09,739 --> 00:24:11,449
Do you want to go out?

313
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:13,785
Actually, that was my plan.

314
00:24:13,869 --> 00:24:16,329
So? Let’s go? Let’s go out.

315
00:24:16,413 --> 00:24:20,083
What did Mr. Mikoy D. Pinagpala eat today?

316
00:24:21,042 --> 00:24:22,460
Whatever it is,

317
00:24:22,961 --> 00:24:25,881
keep eating it
because I like this version of you.

318
00:24:25,964 --> 00:24:28,758
Didn’t I tell you I’ll make it up to you?

319
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:32,554
It’s true that I owe you a lot.

320
00:24:32,637 --> 00:24:34,389
I haven’t had time for you.

321
00:24:34,973 --> 00:24:37,017
I might get used to this.

322
00:24:38,101 --> 00:24:39,519
So? Shall we go?

323
00:24:45,275 --> 00:24:48,445
<i>It’s so humanizing that you’re with Mikoy.</i>

324
00:24:48,528 --> 00:24:52,616
<i>I spent the whole day with Mikoy,</i>
<i>and he has a lot of corny pickup lines.</i>

325
00:24:52,699 --> 00:24:54,159
<i>Do you know what it’s called?</i>

326
00:24:54,242 --> 00:24:55,785
Affection.

327
00:24:55,869 --> 00:24:57,037
Love.

328
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:58,205
<i>Who is that?</i>

329
00:24:58,288 --> 00:24:59,539
<i>Chiara Valtrovi.</i>

330
00:24:59,623 --> 00:25:01,791
<i>We need to involve his daughter.</i>

331
00:25:01,875 --> 00:25:03,752
We need to smoke them out.

332
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:06,087
So we can wipe out those pests.

333
00:25:14,679 --> 00:25:16,389
We need a party!

334
00:25:16,473 --> 00:25:17,724
A celebration!

335
00:25:17,807 --> 00:25:19,267
No need for a welcoming party.

336
00:25:19,351 --> 00:25:23,104
It’s time for the whole Philippines

337
00:25:23,188 --> 00:25:25,190
to meet the Valtrovi family.
